$ Excel Object Model: range.specialCells

The `specialCells` method of the → Microsoft/Office/Excel/Object-Model/Range[`range`] object returns a (sub-)range that consists of the cells that match certain criterias.

The first argument is mandatory and controls what cell-type is included in the returned range.
-
The second argument is optional and controls what → Microsoft/Office/Excel/data-types[data type] a cell must have in order to be returned. The values for these data types are found
→ Microsoft/Office/Excel/functions/type[here] (they correspond to the excel function `type`).

